fields.description:
{{AdminHelper}} and {{CryptAdmin}} where prints message to stdout instead of stderr. Since other failure cases prints to stderr, it is necessary to consolidate that manner.

e.g.
{code}
      if (args.size() != 1) {
        System.err.println("You must give exactly one argument to -help.");
        return 0;
      }
{code}

comments.body:
[~andrew.wang] Thank you for comments.

{quote}
if we're printing to stderr and it's a fatal error, shouldn't it also return a non-zero return code?
{quote}

Ideally it should return a non-zero code I think. As described the document you introduced, error such as invalid argument should be printed into stderr and 
other CLI like {{CryptCLI}} returns non-zero code.

{code}
    public int run(Configuration conf, List<String> args) throws IOException {
      final String path = StringUtils.popOptionWithArgument("-path", args);

      if (!args.isEmpty()) {
        System.err.println("Can't understand argument: " + args.get(0));
        return 1;
      }
  }
{code}

But in terms of return code it can affect client side, I think it might be necessary to take care.

{quote}
it would be nice to test the error codes though.
{quote}
I'll update to add test code to check error code.
